My latest article published on the Express Tribune Blogs; I’d would love to know everyone’s feedback on this vital topic.
Also, a shout-out to one of my favorite (read: sane) men from the Pakistani entertainment industry, Adnan Malik, who took out the time to speak to me for his woke insight! 🙏🏻✨
@adnanmalik1
.
.
.
"In a society where women have to endure life threatening consequences to even report crimes against them, the last thing they need is for prominent personalities to suggest this is just a ‘card’ they use to their benefit,"
-HiraHyder
.
.
.

@adnanmalik1 Will definitely keep reaching out for more!🙌🏻
Such an important piece @hirahyderscribbles! Thank you for reaching out to me 🙏🏼✨
@thewordhaven I’m truly overwhelmed by such a positive feedback, thank you so much sweetheart, means a lot to me!🙏🏻

Such a powerful piece and written with so much eloquence and strength! Shedding light on such issues is so important and it takes the courageous to put their foot down and take a stand. You are no doubt an inspiration to so many and this was definitely the best of all your news stories 👏🏼 👏🏼
@amrasz thank YOUUU Amma for being the inspirational woman who I can look upto♥️

A great article by my Hira Hyder. 
Proud of you meri beti for not being an illiterate westernized feminist but  being well balanced about such touchy and sensetive issue.
@sadafsaysit so glad the article resonated with you!☺️
So well written. Thank you for writing said. We can't say this enough.
@saharmumbles You’ve put it into words brilliantly, couldn’t agree more!

I love it, people forget that there are a few bad apples everywhere, in every situation, in every movement, and that doesn’t belittle or take anything away from the good a revolution is doing, and a revolution this is. Women need to speak up and the society has to learn what victim-shaming is and consciously refrain from it.

node.accessibility_caption: Image may contain: text that says 'However, not everyone is ignorant like Abbasi and Iqbal, and not everyone in the media industry considers harassment to not be a real problem. In the midst of this darkness, there are some who prove to be the voice of rationality.'
